# TextGenSystem

## Purpose
Drives in-engine text generation (ADR 0009). Returns early until the engine config and resource map
exist. Lazily creates the text-gen backend + job + result singletons (deferred), then loads the
resident GGUF language model once from the resource map's language-model paths. Each frame it reaps a
finished Text Gen Job — writing the completion string into the TextGenResultSingletonComponent under the
caller-assigned target UUID — and, while idle and the backend is loaded, assembles one GenerateTextRequest
into backend job parameters (resolving Text Generation Config defaults) and launches a single generation
on a background worker thread so the frame loop never blocks. Only one job runs at a time; overlapping or
not-ready requests are dropped.

Unlike DiffusionSystem (whose result must route through ResourceManagerSystem because the renderer reads
textures only from the resource map under the one-writer rule), text is not a renderer resource, so
TextGenSystem is itself the sole writer of the result store and publishes the completion directly.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| GenerateTextRequestOneFrameComponent | read | App-emitted request: prompt, optional system prompt, config overrides, seed, target UUID |
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | read | Resident GGUF language-model paths (`m_LanguageModelMap`) |
| EngineConfigSingletonComponent | read | Text Generation Config defaults for unset request fields |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| TextGenBackendSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once (holds the platform backend); m_LoadAttempted guards the one-time model load |
| TextGenJobSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Holds the single active/just-finished job (worker thread + atomic state + result string) |
| TextGenResultSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | The result store (target UUID → completion); written when a job completes |
